main event: On July 13, 1965, an unidentified aerial phenomenon was reported in Toronto, Canada, resembling an artificial satellite.
interesting points: The object was observed in flight from NW to SE for a duration of 22 days., The witnesses noted that the weather was clear during the observation., The object was not identified as any known satellites like ECHO I, II, PEGASUS I, II., The report documented an investigation carried out by the U.S. Air Force., It was suggested that the sightings could be attributed to conditions in the satellite operations.
sighted object: unidentified aerial phenomenon resembling an artificial satellite
witness description: No specific witness descriptions were provided.
